    "The idea is that every state x belongs to a chain x 0 ⊒ x 1 ⊒ x 2... that 13 Our use of the term 'refinability' comes from Humberstone [1981].",
    "It is not to be confused with other uses of 'refined' in modal logic, e.g., refined general frames as in Blackburn et al. 2001, Def.",
    "Van Benthem [1981] uses 'cofinality' for the same idea, but given our flipped perspective noted in Remark 2.2, we would have to talk of 'coinitiality'.",
